The consecutive summer days (CSU, Figure 6) in July 2018 are defined as the consecutive number of days with maximum temperature above 25&#176;C. As expected, in southern Europe the number of CSU is greater than in northern Europe. In central and northern Europe the period of warm days was interrupted by days with maximum temperatures below 25&#176;C and therefore the longest periode of warm days is (except for southern Europe) about 10 days or below.
<br><br>
<a href="../images/jul2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_csu_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_CSU_baselayers_overlay_2018-07-16T00-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/jul2018/Stateofclimate_Indices_csu_2018_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_CSU_baselayers_overlay_2018-07-16T00-00-00Z.png" ></a>
